'''Personal imaging''' is the continuous [[real time (media)|realtime]] capturing, archiving, recording,
and sharing of personal [[experience]] through [[image]]s. Typically the images are accompanied by other media such as [[sound reproduction|audio]]visual streams, or with [[writing|text]]ual narratives such as [[diary|diaries]], and often in an interactive way, i.e. people viewing the images comment on the images in realtime while they are being captured, so as to influence the capture process.{{Citation needed|date=August 2009}}

