The ''' Rubus arcticus''' is an annual cultural grant awarded by the County Council of Norrbotten County. The grant is named after the scientific name for the [[Rubus arcticus|nagoon]], which is the [[Province flowers of Sweden|provincial flower of Norrbotten]].
The grant is a development grant worth 100,000 SEK awarded to professional artists. From 1995 until 1998, it was awarded twice a year, once in the spring and once in the fall, to four artists each time<ref name="ra">{{cite web |url=https://www.norrbotten.se/Kultur/Bidrag-stod-och-stipendier/Stipendier/Rubus-Arcticus/Alla-arens-Rubus-Arcticus/ |title= Alla årens Rubus Arcticus-stipendiater |trans-title= All Rubus Arcticus recipients |date= November 24, 2017 |publisher= Region Norrbotten |access-date= August 10, 2018 |language= sv}}</ref>. From 1998 until 2001, it was awarded to eight artists once a year<ref name="ra"/>. Since 2001, the grant has been awarded to four artists once a year<ref name="ra"/>.
